SpeexDSP is a patent-free, Open Source/Free Software DSP library derived
from the Speex codec.  It provides the following features:

  - Resampler
  - Echo canceller
  - Noise suppressor / preprocessor
  - Automatic gain control (AGC)
  - Voice activity detection (VAD)
  - Jitter buffer


== Building with Autotools ==

See the INSTALL file for generic autoconf/automake instructions.

    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure
    make
    make install

Selected ./configure options:

    --enable-fixed-point      Use fixed-point arithmetic (default: float)
    --disable-float-api       Disable the floating-point API
    --disable-examples        Do not build example programs


== Building with CMake ==

A CMake build is available as an alternative to the autotools build.
A build directory separate from the source tree is recommended.

    cmake -S . -B build
    cmake --build build
    cmake --install build

CMake options (pass with -D<OPTION>=<VALUE>):

    BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON|OFF    Build shared instead of static library
                                (default: OFF)
    USE_FIXED_POINT=ON|OFF      Use fixed-point arithmetic
                                (default: OFF, i.e. floating-point)
    CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=...        Release, Debug, RelWithDebInfo, etc.
    CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=...    Installation prefix (default: /usr/local)

Examples:

    # Shared library, release build
    cmake -S . -B build -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build
    cmake --install build

    # Fixed-point, install to /usr
    cmake -S . -B build -DUSE_FIXED_POINT=ON -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr
    cmake --build build
    cmake --install build

== Using speexdsp in a CMake project ==

After installation the library can be found via find_package:

    find_package(speexdsp REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(my_target PRIVATE speexdsp::speexdsp)

pkg-config is also supported:

    pkg-config --cflags --libs speexdsp

== Building with Meson ==

Requires Meson (0.59 or higher), and Ninja.

    rm -rf build
    meson setup build
    ninja -C build

Refer to ./meson_options.txt for options.

== Running CheckASM (SIMD tests/benchmarks) ==

    rm -rf build
    meson setup build -Dbuildtype=release -Dc_args="-O3" -Dtests=enabled
    ninja -C build
    ./build/tests/checkasm --bench --duration=30000 --repeat=5

